1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:07,034
A single approved policy change can leave five operational documents telling five different stories.

2
00:00:07,034 --> 00:00:12,603
CascadeOps turns that follow-through into a reviewable compilation workflow.

3
00:00:12,603 --> 00:00:19,742
This public demo uses deterministic simulated fixture data, clearly labelled Replay Mode.

4
00:00:19,742 --> 00:00:27,319
Our source refund clause changes from thirty days to fourteen, with stable clause and change identifiers.

5
00:00:27,319 --> 00:00:41,765
CascadeOps traces that clause through a curated set of dependencies and proposes five bounded edits: a support SOP, request form, response template, QA checklist, and training guide.

6
00:00:41,765 --> 00:00:47,048
Every proposal cites its exact target anchor and source change.

7
00:00:47,048 --> 00:00:51,082
Human authority is enforced, not implied.

8
00:00:51,082 --> 00:00:56,224
I can reject a patch, and candidate compilation fails closed.

9
00:00:56,224 --> 00:01:00,051
I can revise that decision before compilation.

10
00:01:00,051 --> 00:01:05,837
Only when all five proposals are explicitly approved does the workflow continue.

11
00:01:05,837 --> 00:01:13,814
Now CascadeOps applies all five replacements atomically to isolated, in-memory candidate copies.

12
00:01:13,814 --> 00:01:18,028
The state says candidate compiled, not verified.

13
00:01:18,028 --> 00:01:22,255
No enterprise file or repository is modified.

14
00:01:22,255 --> 00:01:26,417
Verification is a separate, model-free action.

15
00:01:26,417 --> 00:01:37,667
Twenty deterministic assertions check that stale values are absent, the new value is present, anchors remain intact, and untouched blocks are unchanged.

16
00:01:37,667 --> 00:01:41,211
Only then do the candidates become verified.

17
00:01:41,211 --> 00:01:46,817
The receipt records the run, decision totals, and assertion evidence.

18
00:01:46,817 --> 00:01:56,288
Its SHA-256 value is a content checksum for integrity comparison, not a digital signature or compliance seal.

19
00:01:56,288 --> 00:02:08,195
Codex served as principal engineer: architecture, strict contracts, compiler, interface, worker coordination, tests, and final evidence audit.

20
00:02:08,195 --> 00:02:20,721
Optional Live Mode uses GPT-5.6 Responses Structured Outputs with request storage disabled through store false, strict validation, and no silent fallback.

21
00:02:20,721 --> 00:02:24,162
A bounded local live smoke proof passed.

22
00:02:24,162 --> 00:02:29,497
CascadeOps: one policy change, every operation aligned.

